@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Noblik" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  Noblik is played on a 7 by 7 tile board that contains 14 diagonal
bars; there are 7 'ascending' bars (bars that go from the lower
left to the upper right of a tile) and 7 'descending' bars (bars
that go from the upper left to the lower right of a tile). An
ascending bar can move horizontally, either to the right or left.
A descending bar can move vertically, either up or down. Anyways,
a coloured line shown on each bar indicates if that bar can move
horizontally or vertically.

  If an ascending bar is at the left or right column of the board,
obviously it can only move in the other direction. The same applies
for a descending bar that is located on the top or bottom row of
the game board.

  Playing the game is pretty simple, click on any tile (occupied by
a bar or not). If there are bars on the same row and/or column that
can move in that direction, each of these bars will move one space
towards the clicked tile.

  When moving bars, make sure that you do not move them so their
ends 'connect' with the ends of other nearby bars. If that happens,
all connected bars will explode and the game will be over. Although,
two bars may be put on the same tile and 'overlap' each other, just
do not try to move them apart afterwards...

  Every time you move a bar, your score will increase by the amount
of moves you have made in the game; first move = 1 point, second
move = 1 + 2 points, third move = 3 + 3 points, fourth move = 6 + 4
points, and so on...

  As you progress in the game, one bar may randomly move at another
position on its row or column, so you have to be careful...

  Have fun!

@endnode

